page.title: 07Traffic Survey Analysis
page.content: {Thursday 4th July} There seems to be a big difference between the number of cars travelling east and west.There could be two reasons for this ,they could either be making an early start to a holiday in the south west or ,as suggested by the greater number of foreign cars travelling west ,they may have been heading for the Plymouth _ Roscoff ferry which leaves mid afternoon. {Saturday 6th July} There is much less heavy transport traffic on Saturdays as most companies only work from Mondays to Saturdays. There was much more holiday traffic than in mid week as most people begin their holidays on Saturday.
